# CEO Review (Build) — CivicQ Landing Page

I verified the build directly (files on disk, site build, backend syntax, data
math, and a live headless render), not just the builder's report.

## What I confirmed works (verified, not assumed)

- **Files present and sized realistically:** `index.html` (347 lines),
  `methodology.html` (134), `styles.css` (645), `charts.js` (214),
  `main.js` (205) in `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/civicq/`.
- **Registry:** `workSamples.js` entry `id: 9`, `slug: "civicq"` is additive,
  no existing entries touched.
- **Site build is clean:** `npm run build` → 44 modules, built in ~0.8s, and
  the demo copies verbatim into `dist/demos/civicq/` (all 5 files present).
- **Backend:** `civicq_blueprint.py` and the two-line `server.py` registration
  both pass `ast.parse`. (Live endpoint behavior is a deploy/deploy-test
  concern, not blocking here.)
- **Spec fidelity:** all 10 section anchors present (`why-it-matters`,
  `features`, `scoring`, `status`, `org-hub`, `funding`, `partners`, etc.),
  `/methodology` page present, status pills present (`pill--live` /
  `pill--dev`, text "Live"/"Development" uppercased by CSS), nonpartisan
