- **Data viz math is correct (the make-or-break ask):** funds breakdown
  amounts [30000,18000,10000,8000,6000,3000] sum to **exactly $75,000**;
  scoring weights [25,20,18,15,12,10] sum to **exactly 100%**.
- **Live render (Playwright headless over the actual files):** both
  `index.html` and `methodology.html` load at `networkidle` with **0 console
  errors and 0 page errors**; the scoring chart `<svg>` actually draws on
  **both** pages (10 SVGs on index, 3 on methodology). The "charts are real
  coded SVG" and "no console errors on first paint" claims hold up.

This is a genuine 10/10 build: 10 spec sections + methodology page, three real
coded visualizations, a real persisted email-capture backend with CSV export,
WCAG work, and responsive layout. Foundation is strong — no REDIRECT needed.

